quote: Films as special as this one are not often seen. [Full review in Spanish]

quote: ... seductive, finely wrought, and gently knowing film...

critic.name: Diana Metzger
publication.name: Brightest Young Things

quote: Watching Luca Guadagnino's sumptuous 1983-set romance feels like you're living inside someone else's cherished memory, hazy but still vivid.
critic.name: Rob Thomas
publication.name: Capital Times (Madison, WI)

quote: The film wonderfully captures the intensity of that first love -carnal, fleeting and unforgettable - that leaves an indelible mark on everyone lucky enough to experience it. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mario Alegre
publication.name: PrÃ³xima Tanda

quote: I defy anyone to find a story of first love -- its triumphs and heartbreaks, its feverish beginnings and its sad endings -- that's as passionate or as moving as the one told in Call Me by Your Name.
critic.name: Sean P. Means
publication.name: Salt Lake Tribune

quote: The most romantic and sexiest film of 2017. A superb love story all across the board. Stays with you long after. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fico Cangiano
publication.name: CineXpress

quote: You can feel the stillness and the heat of this sultry, sensual summer in Italy. This is a glorious romance about falling in love with life itself, and living with gusto.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson
publication.name: Flick Filosopher

quote: ...it's like sitting through your oversharing neighbor's two-hour vacation slideshow.
critic.name: Luke Y. Thompson
publication.name: Forbes

quote: Desire and the flush of first love permeate this haunting film, whose Italian countryside setting echoes the beauty of the sentiments portrayed.
critic.name: Louise Keller
publication.name: Urban Cinefile

quote: An overlong gay coming-of-age tease, "Stealing Beauty," without Liv Tyler, "American Pie" with less...baking.
critic.name: Roger Moore
publication.name: Movie Nation

quote: Ravishingly pleasurable to look at purely as visual abstraction, even before we get in the business of the erotic depictions.
critic.name: Tim Brayton
publication.name: Alternate Ending

quote: Recalls the talky, intellectual, but swoony summer romances of Eric Rohmer.
critic.name: Jeffrey M. Anderson
publication.name: Combustible Celluloid

quote: It is an adaptation that is loving and faithful, but not slavishly so.
critic.name: Boon Chan
publication.name: The Straits Times (Singapore)

quote: There's just so much to discover in director Luca Guadagnino's take on a 2007 novel of the same name: Some beautiful Italian images, a few simply smart exchanges, and an '80s love story pertinent to our times, to name just a few.
critic.name: John Urbancich
publication.name: Your Movies (cleveland.com)

quote: If there is a film that could be described as luscious, this is it.
critic.name: Jan Lee
publication.name: The New Paper (Singapore)

quote: A kind of pastoral Arcadia in which all the senses reign. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Ernesto Diezmartinez
publication.name: Cine VÃ©rtigo

quote: The skill of Guadagnino's film is the time it takes to tease out Elio and Oliver's attraction, and to deepen our investment in how it plays out.
critic.name: Steve Murray
publication.name: ArtsATL

quote: This coming-of-age love story is all texture, tone and nuance...Luca Guadagnino has made a lovely cinematic feather. And it floats down beautifully, riding a soft breeze of melancholy and grace.
critic.name: Tom Long
publication.name: Detroit News

quote: Guadagnino creates an evocative understanding of time and place, generating a sincere picture, and one that taps into the blur of primal longing.
critic.name: Brian Orndorf
publication.name: Blu-ray.com

quote: Could this film be any better? The cinematography beguiles. The dialogue is natural yet artful. The cast is first rate in every way
critic.name: Peg Aloi
publication.name: Arts Fuse

quote: This is not simply a story of an introvert and an extrovert finding love with one another, but a portrait of desire, told with Guadagnino's unique and detailed attention to place.
critic.name: Eloise Ross

quote: Beautifying shot, hauntingly scored and terrifically acted, Call Me By Your Name is a film whose imagery (particularly its final shot) and characters will stay with you for days.
critic.name: James Croot
publication.name: Stuff.co.nz

quote: The biggest achievement of Call Me by Your Name is that it manages to depict something universal about first love and first loss...
critic.name: Rochelle Siemienowicz
publication.name: sbs.com.au

quote: Based on the acclaimed 2007 novel by Andre Aciman, Call Me By Your Name builds slowly, but surely into a truly great work of purely emotive cinema.
critic.name: Leigh Paatsch
publication.name: Herald Sun (Australia)

quote: The most sensual film in ages; a transcendent exploration of first lust, first love, and first heartbreak seen through the eyes of a hormonal teenager.
critic.name: Marlow Stern
publication.name: The Daily Beast

quote: Elio might have come across as a bit of a prat were it not for his flickering, on-the-edge-of-adulthood beauty, which helps to mitigate some of his... actions. His emotional vulnerability in the face of his desire makes him universally accessible.
critic.name: Vicky Roach
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (Australia)

quote: One of the great coming-of-age movies, and also one of the great movies of teasing courtship
critic.name: Stephen Silver
publication.name: Splice Today

quote: Too long at 132 minutes, Guadagnino's Call Me By Your Name still has much that impresses, from the beautiful, sometimes sun-struck cinematography to the occasionally cutting humour to TimothÃ©e's spot-on portrayal of surly teenage awkwardness.
critic.name: David 'Mad Dog' Bradley
publication.name: Adelaide Review

quote: What truly elevates Call Me by Your Name is Michael Stuhlbarg, as the father to Chalamet and the teacher to Hammer, who gets an all-timer monologue that provides extra layers to the story.
critic.name: Brian Formo
publication.name: Collider

quote: The spirit of Eric Rohmer lives vibrantly in the luscious-looking "Call Me by Your Name." But, unfortunately, not his talent.
critic.name: Al Alexander
publication.name: The Patriot Ledger

quote: Enthralling and unforgettable. Yet, reenforces society's belief that the penis is ugly. Could physically gifted Armie Hammer has an ugly penis?
critic.name: Victoria Alexander
publication.name: FilmsInReview.com

quote: This is, in the end, a simple and beautiful love story-a 'Brief Encounter' that happens to be gay, told with humanity and heart-wrenching truth. It is also, of course, one of the year's very best films.
critic.name: Frank Swietek
publication.name: One Guy's Opinion

quote: The film luxuriates in the sun-kissed settings, languorous and largely devoid of conflict. It's an awfully nice movie, maybe even too nice?
critic.name: Sean Burns
publication.name: The ARTery

quote: Hammer is exceptionally fine in the film... while Chalamet is perfect as the indecisive youth who is drawn to this exotic stranger in ways he himself can't fully comprehend.
critic.name: David Stratton
publication.name: The Australian

quote: It's a story less about the characters involved than it is about the dynamics between them, a late addition to the Symposium's accounts of the great god Love.
critic.name: Matthew Lickona
publication.name: San Diego Reader

quote: Italy has never looked better on screen than it does in Sayombhu's Mukdeeprom's cinematography...
critic.name: Sarah Boslaugh
publication.name: TheArtsStl

quote: Raw and honest, "Call Me By Your Name" exposes loss of innocence while celebrating the importance of one's first love in a mature, albeit graphic, way.
critic.name: Jonathan W. Hickman
publication.name: Daily Film Fix

quote: Just as the entrancing notes of the Psychedelic Furs' 'Love My Way' float through the Italian night in Call Me By Your Name, so too does the seductive, summertime-set romance's own charms.
critic.name: Sarah Ward
publication.name: Screen International

quote: Set in the northern Italian town of Crema and the surrounding countryside, Call Me By Your Name is a movie marinated in sensual pleasures, not all of them having to do with sex.
critic.name: Robert Denerstein
publication.name: Denerstein Unleashed

quote: Sultry and oh-so sexy, Call Me By Your Name is a masterful piece and romantic enough to win over even the hardest of hearts.
critic.name: Becky Suter
publication.name: TheShiznit.co.uk

quote: The film is a great ode to the power of falling in love and discovering one's own truth and identity through the reflection of another.
critic.name: Rob Dean
publication.name: Bullz-Eye.com

quote: In the role of the young virgin, TimothÃ©e Chalamet is engaging as the story's anchor, yet one couldn't imagine this love-dream without Hammer's presence.
critic.name: David Oppedisano
publication.name: Radio Times

quote: Although the material occasionally steers in the vicinity of a 1980s teen romance directed by Randall Kleiser (Summer Lovers fans, you know who you are), there's enough torment and joy generated to cast a real spell.
critic.name: Robert Horton
publication.name: Seattle Weekly

quote: "Call Me By Your Name" is a visually stunning coming-of-age story that boasts a star-making performance by Chalamet.
critic.name: Calvin Wilson
publication.name: St. Louis Post-Dispatch

quote: An astonishing drama of sexual awakening that explores the exhilarations and anxieties that accompany first love.
critic.name: Frederic and Mary Ann Brussat
publication.name: Spirituality & Practice

quote: [There is] a hole at the center of what would otherwise be-and still, semi-miraculously, is-a very involving, melancholy film.
critic.name: Sean Nelson
publication.name: The Stranger (Seattle, WA)

quote: A love affair is inevitable, but Guadagnino doesn't skim over Elio's prolonged longing, which is what makes Call Me by Your Name most potent as a coming-of-age picture, not a mere romance.
critic.name: Kimberley Jones
publication.name: Austin Chronicle

quote: It's probably best to take the movie for what it is: a look at a young, brilliant man who's trying to figure out his future -- and his sexuality.
critic.name: Charles Ealy
publication.name: Austin American-Statesman

quote: Despite all its pain, love is always worth it, the film argues-and makes you believe.
critic.name: Max Weiss
publication.name: Baltimore Magazine

quote: The film is beautifully shot and the performances are outstanding.
critic.name: Bill Goodykoontz
publication.name: Arizona Republic

quote: Call My By Your Name, written for the screen by James Ivory, harkens back to the glory days of his partnership with the late Ismail Merchant, when the Merchant Ivory brand was an art-house staple.
critic.name: Gary Thompson
publication.name: Philadelphia Daily News

quote: You may not realize how strong the acting is until you replay the movie in your head later.
critic.name: Ty Burr
publication.name: Boston Globe

quote: ... Call Me By Your Name can only be described as a perfect film.
critic.name: Sarah Watt
publication.name: Stuff.co.nz

quote: Isolated in the Lombardy region of Italy in a villa tucked away from the sexual politics of America, the tension of the film arises not purely from the proscribed sexuality but rather the intellectual foreplay.
critic.name: Rubin Safaya
publication.name: Cinemalogue

quote: It's a striking reminder of the power of memory and the idea that love lost isn't love wasted, a message that rings beautifully clear and universal no matter how singular and lasting the story of Elio and Oliver is.
critic.name: Allyson Johnson
publication.name: Cambridge Day

quote: Chalamet is a revelation.
critic.name: Sara Michelle Fetters
publication.name: MovieFreak.com

quote: What distinguish it from the competition are the dialogue and the acting.
critic.name: Kelly Vance
publication.name: East Bay Express

quote: Guadagnino has coaxed from his cast a film unmatched this year for lifelike rhythms and attention to human behavior.
critic.name: Peter Canavese
publication.name: Groucho Reviews

quote: It's a piercing glimpse of a young man's bright, confounding first love, the kind of love that brings disorientation and rhapsody.
critic.name: Chris Vognar
publication.name: Dallas Morning News

quote: Though much of Call Me By Your Name is lovely and well-crafted, it's never quite as subtle as the filmmakers seem to assume.
critic.name: Jesse Hassenger
publication.name: Brooklyn Magazine

quote: Slowly, as if in a delicate tango, the two move toward each other, and "Call Me By Your Name" becomes the story of a connection, both sexual and emotional.
critic.name: Moira MacDonald
publication.name: Seattle Times

quote: a glorious cinematic soak
critic.name: Laura Clifford
publication.name: Reeling Reviews

quote: Few films handle coming of age with as much grace and humanity as Call Me By Your Name and the audience is as transformed by the experience as the characters.
critic.name: Wenlei Ma
publication.name: News.com.au

quote: As a gay love story, told without judgment and without apology, it's something that would have seemed unthinkable not so very long ago - and that feels like progress.
critic.name: David Ehrenstein
publication.name: Los Angeles Blade

quote: Every performance in this film is captivating, and the story is sweet and pure.
critic.name: Paula Farmer
publication.name: culturevulture.net

quote: Most reviewers love it. I don't.
critic.name: Tony Macklin
publication.name: tonymacklin.net

quote: If there's been a better film released during 2017, I haven't seen it.
critic.name: Matthew Toomey
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)

quote: Call Me by Your Name is a perfect, lazy, worry-free day, practically devoid of any real-world concerns and absolutely dripping with intellectual and artistic stimulation, and all manner of sexual enticement.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times

quote: It is incredibly pleasant to spend a couple of hours with characters as unashamedly smart as this. It is rare these days to find English-speaking characters who revel in the pleasures of intellectual discussion, who celebrate each other's braininess.
critic.name: CJ Johnson
publication.name: Film Mafia

quote: By the end of this 132-minute journey, I had grown somewhat weary of the tug of war between the two leads, despite disarming efforts from Hammer and Chalamet.
critic.name: Ken Eisner
publication.name: Georgia Straight

quote: There's a lot of the unspoken in Call Me by Your Name, a perceptive film about lust, jealousy, uncertainty, repression, and, maybe, love.
critic.name: Mark Dujsik
publication.name: Mark Reviews Movies

quote: [The] official synopsis assures us that "Elio's sophistication and intellectual gifts suggest he is already a fully-fledged adult," which neither jibes with the on-screen character nor makes up for the fact that Oliver is clearly a solid decade older.
critic.name: Sherilyn Connelly
publication.name: SF Weekly

quote: A complicated movie, erotic yet never graphic, heartfelt yet highly stylized. Chalamet delivers one of the year's best performances.
critic.name: Rafer Guzman
publication.name: Newsday

quote: ...so seductive, you might not notice there is a troubling streak of hedonism at its core.
critic.name: Josh Larsen
publication.name: LarsenOnFilm

quote: One of the year's most romantic movies, and also one of the best.
critic.name: Peter Howell
publication.name: Toronto Star

quote: It's a rare movie that knows when to move and when to stay still. Call Me By Your Name ... is just such a film, lazy as a late-afternoon dragonfly one moment, rash and rushed as young love the next.
critic.name: Chris Knight
publication.name: National Post

quote: A lot of Call Me By Your Name has a hazy, meandering quality to it. In its final moments, as summer draws to a close, Ivory's script and the performances shift into sharp focus.
critic.name: Alan Zilberman
publication.name: Washington City Paper

quote: ... it's a beautiful coming-of-age story that hasn't been told before.
critic.name: Erika W. Smith
publication.name: Bust Magazine

quote: A spellbinding, almost ecstatically beautiful movie that gains even more heft and meaning in its final transcendent moments.
critic.name: Ann Hornaday
publication.name: Washington Post

quote: "Call Me by Your Name" is enough to make you move to the town of Crema, even if your rational self realizes the director Luca Guadagnino trades in a heightened, miragelike state of mythic yearning.
critic.name: Michael Phillips
publication.name: Chicago Tribune

quote: A coming-of-age story exploring one's first experience with true love and sexual uncertainty, including the hypnotic pleasures of both physical and intellectual affection balanced against bittersweet heartbreak
critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: Both a heartwarming and heartwrenching tale of love, loss and discovery that could be my favorite film of the year. Timothee Chalamet, Armie Hammer and Michael Stuhlbarg give award-caliber performances in a film that is an important as it is beautiful.
critic.name: Mark Ellis
publication.name: Schmoes Know

quote: A deep and complex journey into discovery, Call Me By Your Name is an announcement that Timothee Chalamet is a new force to be reckoned with in cinema. Certainly a top contender for awards this season!
critic.name: Kristian Harloff
publication.name: Schmoes Know

quote: "Call Me By Your Name" is transcendent in its first hour, communicating much through the camera's evocation of nature and the screenplay's clear yet subtle dialogue.
critic.name: Mick LaSalle
publication.name: San Francisco Chronicle

quote: A truly escapist romantic fantasy, the movie is awash in the romance of its setting long before things get serious between its protagonists.
critic.name: Jim Slotek
publication.name: Original Cin

quote: Luca Guadagnino's films are so tangible, you could live inside of them, and you'd be happy to stay there.
critic.name: Simon Miraudo
publication.name: Student Edge

quote: Subtly stirring and sensitive drama - about a sensuous summer that could change the course of a boy's life.
critic.name: Susan Granger
publication.name: SSG Syndicate

quote: I'm still uncertain if I buy 31-year- old Armie Hammer as a 24-year- old, but man, Luca Guadagnino's Call Me by Your Name sure does sell its love story.
critic.name: Aaron Yap
publication.name: Flicks.co.nz

quote: It's a story of first love: impossible, impermanent, and passionate.
critic.name: James Berardinelli
publication.name: ReelViews

quote: Gorgeous Tuscan scenery forms the backdrop for a 17-year-old's coming of sexual age. He has the kind of father we all probably wanted.
critic.name: Harvey S. Karten
publication.name: Shockya.com

quote: In what might be the most romantic movie of the year, Call Me by Your Name dispenses with clichÃ© while focusing on the universal fantasy of first love.
critic.name: Annlee Ellingson
publication.name: L.A. Biz

quote: Luca Guadagnino's tale of budding gay romance in 1980s Italy is one of the most mesmerizing films of the year.
critic.name: David Sims
publication.name: The Atlantic

quote: Compared with. . .any number of films dealing with down-to-earth sexual feelings that go wild. . .Call Me By Your Name is trite. . .Few recent films have so bluntly proclaimed moral pessimism.
critic.name: Armond White
publication.name: National Review

quote: [Call Me by Your Name] won't need to guilt, shame or convince to win people over. Instead this coming-of-age romance resonates something more pervasive.
critic.name: Gary Shannon
publication.name: The Young Folks

quote: Luca Guadagnino's romantic drama Call Me By Your Name sneaks up on you -- by the end, it stings with the lingering ache of a late-summer sunburn.
critic.name: April Wolfe
publication.name: Village Voice

quote: Veteran director James Ivory, the screenwriter here, has adapted Aciman's novel with delicacy and discretion. Guadagnino's visual style, on the other hand, is so swoony that one might require a fainting couch.
critic.name: Carrie Rickey
publication.name: Truthdig

quote: The direction by Luca Guadagnino is reminiscent of Bertolucci's sensitivity at its best, the fabulous cinematography by Sayombhu Mukdeeprom rapturously captures the rich work of art that is Italy in summer, and the actors are to die for.
critic.name: Rex Reed
publication.name: Observer

quote: It's the rare movie that dares to show us what unconditional love is, not just from romantic interests, but also from the people who love us the most and know us the best.
critic.name: Alex Abad-Santos
publication.name: Vox

quote: Gorgeous, lyrical story of first love and desire during an Italian summer hits you right in the heart.
critic.name: Pete Hammond
publication.name: Deadline Hollywood Daily

quote: Call Me by Your Name makes you remember how it felt to realize, as you became an adult, that your best experiences are ephemeral-that by the time you recognize an experience for what it is, it's already a memory.
critic.name: K. Austin Collins
publication.name: The Ringer

quote: Although it ends on a powerful, bittersweet chord, the movie is a bit too determinedly soothing for comfort.
critic.name: Peter Rainer
publication.name: Christian Science Monitor

quote: Guadagnino has made the exploration of love and sexuality his mandate.
critic.name: Don Kaye
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: So assailed are we by reports of harmful pleasures, and of the coercive male will being imposed through lust, that it comes as a relief to be reminded, in such style, of consensual joy.
critic.name: Anthony Lane
publication.name: New Yorker

quote: "Call Me By Your Name" is awash in the magical splendor of beautiful sunshine, luscious foods and first love.
critic.name: Jeanne Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: "Call Me By Your Name" is not simply a movie that will be embraced by the LGBT community. It is a story about love and friendship that should be appreciated by everybody.
critic.name: David Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: Call Me by Your Name burns hot from beginning to end.
critic.name: Matt Patches
publication.name: Thrillist

quote: Call Me By Your Name is a beautiful and powerful coming of age love story with remarkable performances from Armie Hammer and TimothÃ©e Chalamet.
critic.name: Molly Freeman
publication.name: Screen Rant

quote: Luminous, breathtaking, and so extraordinarily intimate one can scarcely believe something so miraculous has been captured in front of a camera by actors, the picture is close to a miracle. "Call Me by Your Name" is a motion picture to cherish.
critic.name: Dustin Putman
publication.name: TheFilmFile.com

quote: Call Me by Your Name is a work that I admired for its technique and performances. I did not, however, enjoy the way it made me feel.
critic.name: Mike McGranaghan
publication.name: Aisle Seat

quote: You don't just watch Luca Guadagnino's movies, you swoon into them.
critic.name: Manohla Dargis
publication.name: New York Times

quote: "Call Me by Your Name is a great love story, and it is also a story about the way that Guadagnino's camera loves and brings out Hammer as an actor who can express joy or inner turmoil with a glance."
critic.name: Dan Callahan
publication.name: House Next Door

quote: There's an ethereal quality to Guadagnino's work that shapes its every moment. The story unfolds as if in a dream, a memory of a sun-swept time when the promise of love emerged and brought with it all that's terrible and wonderful in the world.
critic.name: Robert Levin
publication.name: amNewYork

quote: ... an aesthetic journey that pays off in a stunning third act when the endless summer quickens to light speed and is gone in a flash.
critic.name: Lindsey Bahr
publication.name: Associated Press

quote: Raw, and real, and profoundly, indelibly moving.
critic.name: Glen Weldon
publication.name: NPR

quote: First love is as much about hesitancy as it is about exuberance, and Ivory and Guadagnino perfectly capture that sweet turmoil. This isn't just an instant LGBT classic; this is one of the great movie love stories, for audiences of all stripes.
critic.name: Alonso Duralde
publication.name: TheWrap

quote: Elio and Oliver's relationship has an authentic tenderness under the direction of Luca Guadagnino, who's created the best coming-of-age story in recent years.
critic.name: Garrett Schaffel
publication.name: AARP Movies for Grownups

quote: Call Me by Your Name is one of the great movies of the year.
critic.name: Stephen Rebello
publication.name: Playboy Online

quote: Luca Guadagnino's exquisite adaptation of AndrÃ© Aciman's exquisite novel...casts a truly seductive spell.
critic.name: Gary M. Kramer
publication.name: Gay City News

quote: ... remarkable for how it turns literature into pure cinema, all emotion and image and heady sensation.
critic.name: Alissa Wilkinson
publication.name: Vox

quote: Chalamet, a world away from his fine work in "Lady Bird," is a young actor to watch.
critic.name: Amy Rowe
publication.name: New York Daily News

quote: Strong sexual content, adult themes in gay romance.
critic.name: Michael OrdoÃ±a
publication.name: Common Sense Media

quote: Call Me By Your Name is like a treasured artifact from your youth, back when withering looks from a first love felt like daggers to the heart.
critic.name: Mara Reinstein
publication.name: Us Weekly

quote: The way it explores at length the sweet and sour aspects of first love is worth savoring.
critic.name: Brian Truitt
publication.name: USA Today

quote: .. it isn't just one of the best films of 2017, but it is also what cinema is really all about, too.
critic.name: Gregory Wakeman
publication.name: Metro

quote: The small miracle of the movie isn't just that it tells a gay love story with such unreserved tenderness, but that it makes the fate of a romance not meant to last feel like much more than exquisitely framed filmmaking.
critic.name: Leah Greenblatt
publication.name: Entertainment Weekly

quote: Filmed in luminous 35mm, as attentive to the colors and sounds of nature as it is to the beauty of art, architecture, and yes, Armie Hammer, this is the kind of movie you live in as much as watch.
critic.name: Dana Stevens
publication.name: Slate

quote: This gorgeous story is an aching, haunting summer love that fills your heart with love. True to that summer love feeling, it's hard to shake this one.
critic.name: Courtney Howard
publication.name: SassyMamaInLA

quote: Luca Guadagnino's film of first love is beautiful, capped by a scene I may, happily, never forget.
critic.name: Joanna Langfield
publication.name: The Movie Minute

quote: Swooningly romantic, sensually filmed tale of the summer love affair between a teenage boy and his dad's visiting grad-student intern.
critic.name: Kevin Lally
publication.name: Film Journal International

quote: One of the very best films of the year. Guadagnino, a master cinema sensualist, and his award-caliber actors Chalamet, Hammer and Stuhlbarg create a love story for the ages and a new film classic. Let it in.
critic.name: Peter Travers
publication.name: Rolling Stone

quote: What makes Call Be By Your Name stand out from the films it will be compared to is Guadagnino's play on juxtapositions, which go much deeper than merely an angsty teen with an introspective soul.
critic.name: Susan Kemp
publication.name: PopMatters

quote: A lush and vibrant masterpiece about first love set amid the warm, sunny skies, gentle breezes and charming, tree-lined roads of northern Italy.
critic.name: Christy Lemire
publication.name: RogerEbert.com

quote: Languor, lust; yearning, yielding: Call Me by Your Name-a sexy, melancholy summer idyll directed by the supreme cine-sybarite Luca Guadagnino-lushly shows how desire is deftly articulated, even when not explicitly labeled or spoken.
critic.name: Melissa Anderson
publication.name: 4Columns

quote: There is no sin, it insists. There is just joy - and whether you find that in a cold glass of apricot juice or the warm embrace of a village beauty should matter to no one but you.
critic.name: Stephen Whitty
publication.name: Newark Star-Ledger

quote: A lovely place to visit but not particularly absorbing as a narrative, even though Armie Hammer gives an impressive performance.
critic.name: William Bibbiani
publication.name: IGN Movies

quote: Refreshingly fun, erotic, non-judgmental and both intellectually and emotionally smart.
critic.name: Bob Strauss
publication.name: Los Angeles Daily News

quote: [Call me By Your Name] gracefully weaves an examination of internalized homophobia and anti-Semitism, among other things, into its slow-burn romance.
critic.name: Angelo Muredda
publication.name: Cinema Scope

quote: It's a rare remembrance of love that knows the heartbreak after is just as tied up in the experience as the joy during. More, perhaps.
critic.name: Jason Bailey
publication.name: Flavorwire

quote: Call Me by Your Name is more invitingly heartfelt and less baroque than the director's previous films, and skillfully captures ... the languor of the summer mood.
critic.name: Molly Haskell
publication.name: Film Comment Magazine

quote: Chalamet, however, is mesmerizing in the film. He carries the weight of the emotional layers so beautifully and effortlessly.
critic.name: Candice Frederick
publication.name: Reel Talk Online

quote: The achievement of the director Luca Guadagnino is to create in the absence of any obvious opposition a picture that is still taut with inner tensions.
critic.name: Ryan Gilbey
publication.name: New Statesman

quote: Luca Guadagnino's latest is both alluring and alienating in equal measure. That's part and parcel of its beauty.
critic.name: Siddhant Adlakha
publication.name: Birth.Movies.Death.

quote: Call Me By Your Name is a very tasteful exercise. This is one of those movie environments that admits only the intelligent, the well-dressed and the culturally sophisticated.
critic.name: Donald Clarke
publication.name: Irish Times

quote: Guadagnino hasn't adapted Aciman's novel so much as interrogated its moods, going at it con brio.
critic.name: Tom Shone
publication.name: Sunday Times (UK)

quote: Based on Andre Aciman's novel, this gorgeous-looking and beautifully atmospheric film has echoes of all sorts of good things, including Guadagnino's A Bigger Splash and I Am Love.
critic.name: Matthew Bond
publication.name: The Mail on Sunday (UK)

quote: Heat hangs heavy in the air in this beguiling, almost overpoweringly sensual drama, which is languidly paced, and filled with the sleepy sights and sounds of a northern Italian summer.
critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent

quote: Chalamet, with his restless, impatient physicality and a face as sensual and sculpted as a fallen angel from a Caravaggio painting, is quite simply astonishing.
critic.name: Wendy Ide
publication.name: Observer (UK)

quote: What sets this movie apart is the way it creates characters who feel like they have vivid, full lives even when they're not on-screen. So as they collide and connect, everything feels organic and full of possibilities.
critic.name: Rich Cline
publication.name: Contactmusic.com

quote: Whether a paternal benediction is what Elio can or wants to hear, Call Me By Your Name is right to speak it. Philosophically as well as visually, this movie is a beaut.
critic.name: Matt Wolf
publication.name: The Arts Desk

quote: The camera pays an almost hyperreal attention to detail, poring over certain words and touches with the obsessiveness of an infatuated teenager.
critic.name: Catherine Wheatley
publication.name: Sight & Sound

quote: What makes this film special? Aside from the fluid script, inventive camerawork and three uncanny songs by Sufjan Stevens, it's surely the acting, which seems scooped from the performers' marrow.
critic.name: Charlotte O'Sullivan
publication.name: London Evening Standard

quote: It's a nicely observed film, rich in period and mood, and lifted by one really superb performance, by young Chalamet.
critic.name: Brian Viner
publication.name: Daily Mail (UK)

quote: Graceful, heartfelt and infused with a generous spirit, this is a rare and lovely drama.
critic.name: Allan Hunter
publication.name: Daily Express (UK)

quote: A mediocre film would use Elio's parents as a one-note backdrop to his affair: oblivious, disbelieving, disapproving or draconian. Here they are none of those things.
critic.name: Ed Potton
publication.name: Times (UK)

quote: The two leads are utterly superb, but it's Chalamet who delivers a damned flawless performance as the virginal and inquisitive Elio - as expressive as he is captivating.
critic.name: Jamie East
publication.name: The Sun (UK)

quote: What makes the film so magical is the extraordinary delicacy, formal daring and insight with which Guadagnino tackles such familiar material.
critic.name: Geoffrey Macnab
publication.name: Independent (UK)

quote: The performances are casually brilliant...
critic.name: Alistair Harkness
publication.name: Scotsman

quote: The twists and turns here will mirror something - or better still someone - from your own life as the story unfolds in drawing rooms, piazzas, discos and bars. If every film flowed as beautifully as this one we'd rarely see daylight.
critic.name: Harry Guerin
publication.name: RTÃ (Ireland)

quote: Saturated with poetic languor and a deeply sophisticated sensuality.
critic.name: Peter Bradshaw
publication.name: Guardian

quote: It's an incomparably lovely period romance, as warm and therapeutic as the sunlight that suffuses every frame.
critic.name: Robbie Collin
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (UK)

quote: Powerfully emotional and exquisitely romantic, this is a beautifully made and wonderfully acted film that has every element working together in perfect harmony.
critic.name: Matthew Turner
publication.name: iNews.co.uk

quote: ... a work as heart-warming as it is gorgeous.
critic.name: Stephen Porzio
publication.name: Film Ireland Magazine

quote: The film's genius is that it never settles into a steady track. Shots are often held too long or too short, by orthodox rules. Piano runs suddenly ambush the soundtrack.
critic.name: Nigel Andrews
publication.name: Financial Times

quote: A beautiful film about love and longing, one you'll want (and need) to watch again and again and again.
critic.name: Adam Woodward
publication.name: Little White Lies

quote: Peachy keen. A luminous, sun-kissed Italian love story brimming with warmth, passion and feeling. This is utterly unmissable.
critic.name: Josh Winning
publication.name: Total Film

quote: Call Me by Your Name an ode to love and its precipices... [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Erick Estrada
publication.name: Cinegarage

quote: Part heady romance, part coming-of-age tale, and one of the most beautiful recent examples of both.
critic.name: Josh Slater-Williams
publication.name: The Skinny

quote: Though Call Me By Your Name overall is a little disappointing, especially after all the hype it has received, these final scenes are inarguably majestic.
critic.name: Chloe Walker
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: This is exquisite filmmaking, from an aesthetically accomplished director who you can feel falling in love with these characters as much as the audience are.
critic.name: Alistair Ryder
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: I wasn't enamoured by Call My By Your Name until its final half hour, by which point I was swept away in a sea of love, longing and, ultimately, loss.
critic.name: Ryan Morris
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: This is an erotic and mesmerizing movie that exemplifies cinematic artistry in scope, theme, and tone.
critic.name: Jordan Ruimy
publication.name: World of Reel

quote: A film that's at once light, joyful and emotionally devastating, with deeply affecting central performances. A full-hearted romantic masterpiece.
critic.name: Olly Richards
publication.name: Empire Magazine

quote: Call Me By Your Name thinks about cruising and playing games, but never makes up its mind.
critic.name: Kyle Turner
publication.name: Paste Magazine

quote: Not only offers a feast for your eyes, but also imagery so evocative it'll make your heart race and your fingers tingle with the memory of sun and touches from summers past.
critic.name: Kristy Puchko
publication.name: Pajiba

quote: There's something quite touching about watching Stuhlbarg in Call Me by Your Name eight years after his breakthrough in A Serious Man.
critic.name: Adam Nayman
publication.name: Reverse Shot

quote: Anchored by a duo of riveting performances by TimothÃ©e Chalamet and Armie Hammer, "Call Me by Your Name" is a spiritual and effervescent experience.
critic.name: Clayton Davis
publication.name: AwardsCircuit.com

quote: Call Me by Your Name is a fairly straightforward coming-of-age story that's at its finest in moments when the relationships take on larger meanings than their literal context implies, and Luca Guadagnino finds evocative aesthetic expressions for them.
critic.name: Sam C. Mac
publication.name: Slant Magazine

quote: Come for the buzz around a scandalous peach scene, stay for the viscous chemistry between the two leads.
critic.name: Alexandra Pollard
publication.name: Dazed and Confused

quote: Italy has never looked so inviting.
critic.name: Dwight Brown
publication.name: National Newspaper Publishers Association

quote: A melancholic film that will inevitably evoke this singular restlessness of the first love. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Oscar Uriel
publication.name: Cinema Movil

quote: Call Me By Your Name warmly embraces the fickleness of first love, the confusing elements of queer desire, and-above all-the tranquility of total togetherness.
critic.name: Tomas Trussow
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: [Call Me By Your Name] may be the best new film I've seen this year.
critic.name: John Powers
publication.name: Vogue

quote: A timeless romance with a preserved space in the books of cinema history. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Orlando Maldonado
publication.name: Movie Network

quote: The "somewhere in Northern Italy" setting is a character all its own in the movie with its hidden ponds, cute towns, and a rustic villa.
critic.name: Jason Guerrasio
publication.name: Business Insider

quote: It can try the patience.
critic.name: Kate Taylor
publication.name: Globe and Mail

quote: The film's heart is found not with the two leads but in a gut-wrenching monologue by Michael Stuhlburg as Elio's father.
critic.name: Glenn Sumi
publication.name: NOW Toronto

quote: Filled with moments of pure bliss, this deeply touching film is a romance for the ages.
critic.name: Shane Slater
publication.name: AwardsCircuit.com

quote: Yes, a lot of these elements can be universal, but it seems undeniable to me that a gay audience will bring something altogether unique to their viewing of such a film.
critic.name: Glenn Dunks
publication.name: Junkee

quote: The film makes a defense of erudition as another pleasure of life, comparable to the discovery of sexuality and the first love that moves its main story. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Miguel MuÃ±oz Garnica
publication.name: El antepenÃºltimo mohicano

quote: Call Me By Your Name succeeds as it offers a central queer romance as a bond based on true love and understanding, a connection that can be formed by all.
critic.name: Alex Lines
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: Call Me by Your Name is a masterpiece.
critic.name: George Fenwick
publication.name: New Zealand Herald

quote: Viewers don't just witness a 17-year-old boy become infatuated, nor understand it; they feel as though they're in the exact same situation themselves.
critic.name: Sarah Ward
publication.name: Goethe-Institute Australien Magazine

quote: Guadagnino's new film is also his sweetest, calmest, and loveliest. It sneaks up on you. Throughout, Guadagnino captures what first love feels like, in all its fumbling, awkward, confusing, terrifying, joyous glory.
critic.name: Alex Heeney
publication.name: Seventh Row

quote: First love has rarely been depicted as beautifully or as movingly as it is in Luca Guadagnino's Call Me By Your Name, an adaptation of the AndrÃ© Aciman.
critic.name: Angie Han
publication.name: Slashfilm

quote: The story that stories about first love will be judged against for many years to come.
critic.name: Sarah Ward
publication.name: Concrete Playground

quote: The bond between Elio and Oliver grows tentatively, but unleashes forceful emotions that reverberate through all the relationships in a film both hilarious and gorgeously sad, that crackles with sexual tension.
critic.name: Carmen Gray
publication.name: Dazed and Confused

quote: Stripped of the baggage that so often complicates and corrupts queer romance, Call Me by Your Name is allowed to flourish as an unfiltered evocation of the agony and ecstasy of first love.
critic.name: Paul O'Callaghan
publication.name: Sight & Sound

quote: Luca Guadagnino's film proves affecting as a chronicle of a young man learning to embrace his more emotional side.
critic.name: Kenji Fujishima
publication.name: Slant Magazine

quote: A major addition to the queer cinema canon.
critic.name: Patrick Gamble
publication.name: CineVue

quote: The film triumphs thanks to Chalamet's performance, as it's hard to recall seeing a young actor turn in as accomplished a performance as he manages here.
critic.name: Stefan Pape
publication.name: HeyUGuys

quote: Equally a portrayal of good parenting as it is honest sexual becoming.
critic.name: Fred Topel
publication.name: Nerd Report

quote: In attaching sinuous style and casual sexiness to a universal ache, [Luca] Guadagnino has come away with real wisdom. Sweet and salty, his movie burns like a suntan.
critic.name: Joshua Rothkopf
publication.name: Time Out

quote: Feels both fresh and vintage, and watching it, you can almost feel the warm Italian sun and smell the fresh breeze billowing through the orchards. A trip to a bucolic place of young love and intellectual rigour, it's an intoxicating work.
critic.name: Jason Gorber
publication.name: ScreenAnarchy

quote: Committed with the utmost beauty, humanity, and sexuality.
critic.name: Michael Arbeiter
publication.name: Nerdist

quote: Guadagnino's film is one of swooning sentiment, but it never once cheapens or diminishes the rich emotion of its story for extraneous impact.
critic.name: Dominick Suzanne-Mayer
publication.name: Consequence

quote: It's hard to think of many movies that have so successfully appealed to both the intellectual and the erotic since the heydays of Patrice ChÃ©reau and AndrÃ© TÃ©chinÃ©.
critic.name: Sam Adams
publication.name: BBC.com

quote: An effortlessly beautiful ode to the loves destined to last a lifetime even when those we love are no longer in our lives.
critic.name: Rob Hunter
publication.name: Film School Rejects

quote: Call Me by Your Name achieves a rush of nostalgia for first love and first loss.
critic.name: Tyler Coates
publication.name: Esquire Magazine

quote: Drenched in sunlight, the movie is filled with warmth (and hotness), devoid of sappy melodrama but rich with honest emotion that transcends boundaries of sexual orientation.
critic.name: Eric D. Snider
publication.name: EricDSnider.com

quote: Unforgettable on every level, the kind of film that has the power to move and inspire.
critic.name: Brian Tallerico
publication.name: RogerEbert.com

quote: A swirling wonder, a film about coming of age, about the secrets of youth, the magic of summer, the beauty of Italy.
critic.name: Richard Lawson
publication.name: Vanity Fair

quote: Any of Guadagnino's cinematic trips to sunny Italy are worth taking, but Call Me By Your Name may be his most tender and sumptuous work yet.
critic.name: Oliver Whitney
publication.name: ScreenCrush

quote: A powerfully erotic and affecting love story, albeit one so closely and intimately observed that the term "slow burn" seems almost inadequate.
critic.name: Justin Chang
publication.name: Los Angeles Times

quote: A sumptuously filmed, beautifully acted love story with Armie Hammer's best performance to date.
critic.name: Chris Bumbray
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network

quote: A feat of accentuated sound design and arresting cinematography, luxuriating in the beauty of Italy.
critic.name: Jordan Raup
publication.name: The Film Stage

quote: The final beats of Guadagnino's adaptation galvanize two hours of simmering uncertainty into a gut-wrenchingly wistful portrait of two people trying to find themselves before it's too late.
critic.name: David Ehrlich
publication.name: indieWire

quote: Call Me By Your Name is a triumph of humanity.
critic.name: Mike Ryan
publication.name: Uproxx

quote: Based on AndrÃ© Aciman's 2007 novel, Luca Guadagnino directs a sexy, stunning film that will tunnel its way into your heart and live there.
critic.name: Meredith Borders
publication.name: Birth.Movies.Death.

quote: Call Me By Your Name's erotic tension wouldn't crackle so loudly without the chemistry between its leads.
critic.name: A.A. Dowd
publication.name: AV Club

quote: 'Call Me by Your Name' is a triumph in every regard
critic.name: Adam Chitwood
publication.name: Collider
